    "body": "Attempting to download large files using send_file with X-Sendfile headers did not work with Python 2.7.2, Apache 2.2.20 on Ubuntu 11.10, only an empty file was downloaded. Setting the \"Content-Length\" header solved the issue. I can't see why it would hurt to always have it there since response content is discarded when using X-Sendfile anyway.\n",
